Understanding ASCII and Unicode (GCSE)

OSI (Open Systems Interconnect) Model

OSI 7 layers
Layer 1 - Physical (Bits)
Layer 2 - Data Link - Frame or Mac (MAC Address)
Layer 3 - Network - Logical Address - Packets (IPv4 and IPv6)
Layer 4 - Transport (Reliability) -TCP & UDD
Layer 5 - Session - Start, Maintain, Stop
Layer 6 - Presentation - Data Format Translation = ASCI/Unicode, Encryption, Compression
Layer 7 - Application - Network Ports

All           People         Seem      To          Need      Dominos     Pizza  
Application   Presentation   Session   Transport   Network   Data Link   Physical
